Official Music Video for "Billie Jean" by Michael Jackson
Listen to more of your favorites by Michael Jackson: https://MichaelJackson.lnk.to/_listenYD

"Billie Jean" was the first short film made for 'Thriller,' the biggest-selling album of all time. The short film for this No. 1 single, directed by Steve Barron, made history as the first video by a black artist to receive heavy rotation on MTV, and was later ranked by the network as one of the 100 greatest music videos of all time.

Subscribe to the official Michael Jackson YouTube Channel: https://MichaelJackson.lnk.to/subscribeYD

Watch more Michael Jackson videos: https://MichaelJackson.lnk.to/_listenYC/youtube

Follow Michael Jackson: 
Facebook: https://MichaelJackson.lnk.to/_followFI

Instagram: https://MichaelJackson.lnk.to/_followII 
Website: https://MichaelJackson.lnk.to/_followWI 
Spotify: https://MichaelJackson.lnk.to/_followSI

Written & Composed by Michael Jackson
Produced by Quincy Jones for Quincy Jones Productions
Co-Produced by Michael Jackson for MJJ Productions, Inc.
From the album Thriller, released November 30, 1982
Released as a single January 2, 1983

THE SHORT FILM
Director: Steve Barron
Primary Production Location: Los Angeles, California

Michael Jackson's short film for "Billie Jean" was the first of three short films produced for recordings from Thriller, which continues its reign as the biggest selling album of all time with worldwide sales in excess of 105 million as of June 1, 2016 and in December, 2015 became the first ever album to be awarded triple diamond status by the RIAA for US sales alone. The ""Billie Jean"" single reached No. 1 in 10 countries in the spring of 1983, including seven consecutive weeks atop the Billboard Hot 100 - becoming the second-highest selling single in America that same year.

"Billie Jean" was certified Gold by the Recording Industry Association of America on April 4, 1983, and Platinum on February 4, 1989. The song won two Grammy Awards for Best R&B Song and Best R&B Performance - Male, as well as an American Music Award for Favorite Single - Pop/Rock and was also named the Single of the Year on The Village Voice Pazz & Jop critics' poll in 1983.

The short film featured a paparazzo attempting to photograph Jackson as he danced through an urban landscape. A specially created set featured steps and sidewalk tiles that lit up underneath Michael's feet. It is here that fans first saw some of Michael's best-known dance moves, such as spinning and landing on his toes. Many of Michael's steps and mannerisms in the video would become forever associated with The King of Pop.

When the chorus hit.he sprung into this dance that was unlike anything I'd ever seen, director Steve Barron recounted of Jackson's choreography in the video. "It was just extraordinary, instinctive. He pulled it all together and turned it into what we saw.The camera literally steamed up, the eyepiece steamed up, because of my heat from what I was seeing." Barron also recalled the crew breaking into spontaneous applause after Michael finished dancing.

The "Billie Jean" short film made history as the first video by a black artist to be played in heavy rotation on MTV, then in its second year. In 1992, the short film was inducted into the Music Video Producers Hall of Fame. MTV ranked "Billie Jean" as the 35th greatest music video of all time in 1999, one of three entries of Jackson's on the chart alongside "Thriller" and "Beat It."

#MichaelJackson #BillieJean #Thriller

Official video for ‚ÄúRISK, RISK, RISK!‚Äù, the first single from Jhariah‚Äôs upcoming second full-length record: https://onerpm.link/riskriskrisk

It‚Äôs finally here!! I‚Äôve been thinking about this day for such a long such, I can hardly believe the song is really out! 
I started writing RISK in early 2021, while I was finishing Beginner‚Äôs Guide. At that point, I was already pretty deep into writing this next album, but I knew almost instantly that I wanted thos song to be how I introduced this new record to the world. It feels like the perfect encapsulation of this new era for me. At its core, this song and this album are about overcoming fear. The bigger I dream, the more I‚Äôve found fear to be a luxury that I can‚Äôt afford. There‚Äôs just so much I want to do and so many challenges to surmount in the process! That hardly leaves room for me to be an obstacle to myself. Once I started trying to articulate that feeling, I realized that it was quintessential to this new chapter in my life and in my career. A lot of this album is about trust, so this was kind of my moment to write about trusting myself. 

I hope you like it! There‚Äôs so much of myself in this song and I‚Äôm SO proud of it!!! I hope it spurs you to tackle something that scares you or take on a challenge that seems daunting. 

Oh and come out to a show on this upcoming tour and see it live! OK, that‚Äôs it! Much much more to come :) Stay tuned friends.

tracks.track: Five River Flow (Ajj Aakhaan Waris Shah Nu) - Amrit Kaur

youtubeData.title: Amrit Kaur - Five River Flow | Ajj Aakhaan Waris Shah Nu - Amrita Pritam | Partition of India 1947
youtubeData.description:
Thank you for listening to me singing Amrita Pritam's famous poem Ajj Akhaan Waris Shah Nu (there are SO many different spellings) I first read this in Punjabi while studying History at SOAS, University of London and thought - I need to hear this sung by a woman - and at that time I couldn't find any! So I decided to compose my own version expressing my truth and my relation to this dark history. Both sides of my grandparents are from what is now Pakistan. Inspired by the power-house vocals of Reshma, Noor Jahaan, Abida Parveen as well as Etta James, Nina Simone and Aretha Franklin, I sung this in a play I was music directing and since then, it has become the opening of every set I've performed around the world. This was recorded in one-take. The goal was not a perfect performance but it is me finding a way to express the most intense grief of my people, of my family in the most universal way possible - through music.

As heard on BBC Woman's Hour, The Guilty Feminist Podcast & Jaipur Literature Festival.

"Born and raised in Tottenham, Amrit Kaur's music has been described by OZY Magazine as the place 'where Aretha soul meets Punjabi folk'. She is a singer-songwriter, Sarangi player and power-house vocalist in the genres of Soul, R&B and Punjabi folk. Praised by legendary record producer Rick Rubin for her live ability, Amrit Kaur has been named a BBC Introducing artist and a BBC Asian Network Sound of 2020 artist. Her notable performances include Glastonbury Festival, Jaipur Literature Festival, TEDxSOAS and UN General Assembly alongside Skip Marley. During the pandemic, she featured on the new version of 'One Love' by Bob Marley, alongside the Marley family and musicians from around the world in support of UNICEF. Amrit has composed music for BBC Television series and theatre productions. Five River Flow is the first single from her her first EP."

We hope you‚Äôre all safe and sound. As a team, we put in a lot of effort for every single music video we release. But this one was really special for all of us, because all of you made it possible. This time, you guys were the crew & the talent, turning your homes into our set. The hundreds of videos you all sent from across the globe, showing us that nothing can stop you from doing what moves you, not even the lockdown, is what makes this video extraordinary.

We are honored and overwhelmed with all your videos and even though we could not feature all of them, be assured that we have watched every single one of them and felt your energy and joy across borders. THANK YOU! 

You guys truly are a breath of Thandi Hawa! 
This is a celebration of our unity, despite the distancing.
Let this be proof that we came out of this lockdown stronger, livelier, wilder and cooler.

Stay Safe & Do What Moves You. At Home. For Now.
#BacardiSessions #DoWhatMovesYou

P.S - All the rules and regulations related to national lockdown against COVID-19 were adhered to while making the video.
No animals were harmed during the making of the video

Releasing a string of smash hits off his September 2014 debut album ‚ÄúPrayer‚Äù established Robin Schulz as one of the internationally most successful German artists of the past 20 years. Now, the Osnabr√ºck-native, superstar DJ and producer is set to release his highly-anticipated follow-up longplayer: Almost exactly one year after the release of his globally acclaimed breakthrough debut, Schulz is back on track with yet another stroke of genius: Promisingly entitled ‚ÄúSUGAR‚Äù, album no. 2 will be released later this year on September 18th!

Earlier this July, Schulz was awarded Triple Gold for his tremendous hit single ‚ÄúPrayer in C‚Äù, Platinum for ‚ÄúSun Goes Down (feat. Jasmine Thompson)‚Äù as well as Gold for his debut album ‚ÄúPrayer‚Äù in his home territory ‚Äì just 3 on a list of over 60(!) awards already amassed by the German deep house shooting star. In light of his upcoming new longplayer ‚ÄúSUGAR‚Äù, Robin Schulz is now about to take the next step in his amazingly successful career:

After his airplay #1 and global smash single ‚ÄúHeadlights‚Äù (feat. Ilsey) which delivered the first taste of his new album‚Äôs sound, the twentysomething is set to release the eponymous second single on July 17th: ‚ÄúSugar‚Äù, featuring 19-year-old Canadian singer Francesco Yates. Yates is widely considered the next big popstar in the making and his soulful falsetto vocals are quickly gaining praise by superstars such as Pharrell Williams or Justin Bieber.

Available on Deluxe 2-LP, 2-CD, and Digital ‚Äî as well as a Super Deluxe Edition collector‚Äôs box set ‚Äî Fallen (20th Anniversary Edition) offers newly remastered audio, including the album‚Äôs singles ‚ÄúMy Immortal,‚Äù ‚ÄúGoing Under,‚Äù ‚ÄúEverybody‚Äôs Fool,‚Äù and ‚ÄúBring Me To Life.‚Äù The expanded set also includes a trove of bonus material ‚Äì ten tracks in all ‚Äì comprising previously-unreleased demos and live recordings plus a selection of rare B-sides. Alongside reimagined artwork, all physical formats will include previously-unseen photos from the era, plus a handwritten foreword by Amy Lee, who oversaw all aspects of the reissue. The Deluxe vinyl, CD and digital configurations are out now. 

Available exclusively at Evanescence.com is the Super Deluxe Box Set, arriving February, 2024. Housed in a collectible shadow box-style package (inspired by Amy‚Äôs songwriting journal cover art), this limited edition includes all of the above-mentioned music as part of a 2-LP set (featuring a Black & Silver blend vinyl) plus a bonus cassette of previously unreleased demos and voice notes which is exclusive to this box set. Evanescence are celebrating the 20th anniversary of Fallen with a series of special reissues via Craft Recordings. 

Details/order: https://found.ee/fallen20 

Available on Deluxe 2-LP, 2-CD, and Digital ‚Äî as well as a Super Deluxe Edition collector‚Äôs box set ‚Äî Fallen (20th Anniversary Edition) offers newly remastered audio, including the album‚Äôs singles ‚ÄúMy Immortal,‚Äù ‚ÄúGoing Under,‚Äù ‚ÄúEverybody‚Äôs Fool,‚Äù and ‚ÄúBring Me To Life.‚Äù The expanded set also includes a trove of bonus material ‚Äì ten tracks in all ‚Äì comprising previously-unreleased demos and live recordings plus a selection of rare B-sides. Alongside reimagined artwork, all physical formats will include previously-unseen photos from the era, plus a handwritten foreword by Amy Lee, who oversaw all aspects of the reissue. The Deluxe vinyl, CD and digital configurations are out now. 

Available exclusively at Evanescence.com is the Super Deluxe Box Set, arriving February, 2024. Housed in a collectible shadow box-style package (inspired by Amy‚Äôs songwriting journal cover art), this limited edition includes all of the above-mentioned music as part of a 2-LP set (featuring a Black & Silver blend vinyl) plus a bonus cassette of previously unreleased demos and voice notes which is exclusive to this box set. All credits in the description. I'm back with another awards show concept perf type of video! This video is my own imagination that I wanted BLACKPINK to perform this type of concept on any awards show rather than being on cAGe for 2 mins straight standing there if y'all know what i mean... And I put fans' screaming to make this video more realistic. USE EARPHONE FOR A BETTER QUALITY.

-

1:07 BLACKPINK appears on the stage with a badass outfit and their stage presence is on-point! 
1:20 OT4 Breakdance with flashing lights
1:33 Jensoo breakdance and Chaelisa move to the back
1:46 Chaelisa aka the DANCER LINE 1st duo breakdance and Jensoo move aside
2:00 JENNIE solo stage with her powerful & strong rap & different choreo with back-up dancers. The other pinks left the stage already
2:13 Jennie left the stage. All back-up dancers dance with drums when KTL intro started. 
2:30 BLACKPINK come out to the stage again and started performing KTL
3:48 BLACKPINK's second break dance
4:06 The light turn off so back-up dancers and BLACKPINK themselves to get ready for the next performance. 
-
BLACKPINK's real performance is here with their latest songs released this year, How You Like That, Pretty Savage & Lovesick Girls!
-
4:30 HYLT Intro
4:40 BLACKPINK's third break dance (as the opening stage for HYLT)
4:54 The light turn off all of sudden and JenChuChaeng move to the side. 
4:58 LISA's Solo Stage with back-up dancers and different choreo!
5:13 The other pinks move to LISA's side to continue the performance
-
6:12 The transition between HYLT & Pretty Savage. The light turn off again and started lighting up when JISOO shouted the iconic line, 'BLACKPINK IN YOUR AREA'.
6:24 Pretty Savage (Performance) started.
7:38 JISOO's solo stage with a back-up dancers and different choreo. The other pinks move to the back. 
8:31 ROS√â's solo stage. She's walking to the front stage while singing her beautiful brigde part and looking at the BLINKS. The other pinks take another way quickly through backstage as to give ROS√â's spotlight she deserved. 
8:53 Jennie, Lisa & Jisoo joined Ros√© 
-
9:23 The light turn off again and the stage turn so colorful. 
9:27 Lovesick Girls INTRO. The light turn on when the chorus part started. 
10:02 JENLISA's solo stage & the camera only focus on them. LISA dances with a man and push him away. Jennie's shady stage by wearing a doctor cap.
10:18 CHAESOO's solo stage & the camera only focus on them. Same stage as LISA's where ROS√â's push a man (back-up dancer) away and Jisoo dances with back-up dancer with a different choreo.
They are all gather back in chorus part
11:20 BLACKPINK's fourth breakdance!

Evanescence are celebrating the 20th anniversary of Fallen with a series of special reissues via Craft Recordings. 

Details/order: https://found.ee/fallen20 

Available on Deluxe 2-LP, 2-CD, and Digital ‚Äî as well as a Super Deluxe Edition collector‚Äôs box set ‚Äî Fallen (20th Anniversary Edition) offers newly remastered audio, including the album‚Äôs singles ‚ÄúMy Immortal,‚Äù ‚ÄúGoing Under,‚Äù ‚ÄúEverybody‚Äôs Fool,‚Äù and ‚ÄúBring Me To Life.‚Äù The expanded set also includes a trove of bonus material ‚Äì ten tracks in all ‚Äì comprising previously-unreleased demos and live recordings plus a selection of rare B-sides. Alongside reimagined artwork, all physical formats will include previously-unseen photos from the era, plus a handwritten foreword by Amy Lee, who oversaw all aspects of the reissue. The Deluxe vinyl, CD and digital configurations are out now. 

Available exclusively at Evanescence.com is the Super Deluxe Box Set, arriving February, 2024. Housed in a collectible shadow box-style package (inspired by Amy‚Äôs songwriting journal cover art), this limited edition includes all of the above-mentioned music as part of a 2-LP set (featuring a Black & Silver blend vinyl) plus a bonus cassette of previously unreleased demos and voice notes which is exclusive to this box set. Adding additional insight into the album is an expansive book which features new track-by-track notes from Lee, while a zoetropic turntable slipmat, rare photo prints, and enamel pin set round out the collection.

Wagon Christ 'Chunkothy' (Official Video)
youtubeData.description:
Taken from the new Wagon Christ album 'Toomorrow', out now on CD, LP and download: http://bit.ly/hWkL1n. The one and only Luke Vibert returning to the fray - the king of stoned exotica, ridiculous vocal samples, toothsome puns, swinging rhythm and the psychedelic groove, Vibert has never been one to take himself too seriously, but his music continues to delight.

The 'Chunkothy' video is directed and animated by Celyn Brazier at Nexus with Beccy McCray providing invaluable production skills. Bali Engel helped colour and provided the beautiful animated sequences for the insect loop and fishes. Margot Tsakiri-Scanatovits and Manav Dhir also provided colouring skills and contributed to the animation of the insects. Steve Mc Inerney constructed the final edit with perfect timing and imagination.

The animation was created in Photoshop, with most sequences on one layer. It was as simple as that really. No gimmicks, no tweeny motion tricks, no cgi.  Celyn created small beat guides for reference, sometimes following the rhythm, for example on the bouncy ball loops, but mostly as many random patterns and as much weird sh*t that he could possibly make in six weeks. 

Look out for the Mexican cat!
